-- Cardinals Sign Free-Agent Shortstop Peralta to Four-Year Deal
-- B y   J a y   B e b e r m a n
-- 2013-11-25T02:07:48Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-11-25/cardinals-sign-free-agent-shortstop-peralta-to-four-year-deal.html
The St. Louis Cardinals signed free-agent shortstop Jhonny Peralta to a four-year contract, the
Major League Baseball team said on its website.  Peralta, 31, hit .303 with 11 home runs and 55 runs batted
in for the Detroit Tigers last season.  Peralta received a 50-game drug suspension from MLB on Aug.
5 of last season for his involvement with Biogenesis of America
LLC, an anti-aging clinic in  Coral Gables , Florida.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Jay Beberman at 
 jbeberman@bloomberg.net  